          "date": "2025-10-27 22:13:57.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-19525 lod: prevent stranding parity mirrors on deletion",
        "message": "LU-19525 lod: prevent stranding parity mirrors on deletion\n\nErasure coding parity mirrors require a corresponding data mirror\nwith matching extents. Prevent deletion of a data mirror if it\nwould leave a parity mirror without any matching data mirror.\n(A \"parity mirror\" is any mirror containing parity components.)\n\nParity mirrors can always be deleted as they can never be un-stale\nunless their matching data component is ALSO un-stale.\n\nTest-Parameters: forjanitoronly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ie81adbaf3b33794b3b47b976b6e33a8643672cc9\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master",
      "description": "Rebase"
    }
